Victoria police revealed 156 truck drivers tested positive for drugs in the past year . 
  Police said there is a distribution network of speed, ice and marijuana operating in the trucking industry . 
  A former Melbourne truck driver said his colleagues were taking drugs regularly . 
  He said meeting areas were often set up between drivers over radios using codes . 
  One in every 12 truckies tested positive to drugs while on the road . 
 